config MEMMAP_MODULE
    tristate "Quantum Memmap Memory Driver"
    depends on ARM64
    default m
    help
      This driver provides block device access to reserved memory regions.
      It can map physical memory ranges as block devices for use as
      temporary storage (e.g., memdisk at 0x78000000).

      Select this to build the memmap driver as a module (m) or built-in (y).

      Usage:
        insmod memmap.ko memmap=256M\$0x78000000
        mount /dev/memblock0 /mnt/memdisk
